27 class ConstantRotationData():
28  """
29  Class to store dynamic pose data into a nested dictionary.
30  It is stored as in [20 poses][7 excited joints][7 IMUs][data].
31  self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name] = np.ndarray
32  The data is defined as below.
33  data = [acceleration, joint angles, joint velocities].
34  """
35  def __init__(self, pose_names, joint_names, imu_names, filepath):
36  """
37  Initialize StaticPoseData class.
38 
39  Arguments
40  ----------
41  pose_names: list[str]
42  Names of poses
43  joint_names: list[str]
44  Names of joints
45  imu_names: list[str]
46  Names of imus
47  filepath: str
48  Path to save the collected data
49  """
50  self.pose_names = pose_names
51  self.joint_names = joint_names
52  self.imu_names = imu_names
53 
54  self.filepath = filepath
55  self.data = OrderedDict()
56 
57  # Create nested dictionary to store data
58  for pose_name in pose_names:
59  self.data[pose_name] = OrderedDict()
60  for joint_name in joint_names:
61  self.data[pose_name][joint_name] = OrderedDict()
62  for imu_name in self.imu_names:
63  self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name] = np.empty((0, 15), float)

65  def append(self, pose_name, joint_name, imu_name, data):
66  """
67  Append data to a dictionary whose keys are
68  [pose_name][joint_name][self.imu_mappings[imu_name]]
69 
70  Arguments
71  ----------
72  pose_name: str
73  Names of poses
74  joint_name: str
75  Names of joints
76  imu_name: str
77  Names of imus
78  data: np.array
79  Numpy array of size (1,4).
80  Includes an accelerometer measurement and a joint angle.
81  """
82  self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name] = \
83  np.append(self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name], np.array([data]), axis=0)

85  def clean_data(self, verbose=False):
86  """
87  Cleans the data.
88 
89  Arguments
90  ----------
91  `verbose`: `bool`
92  """
93  # Create nested dictionary to store data
94  data = copy.deepcopy(self.data)
95  for pose_name in self.pose_names:
96  for joint_name in self.joint_names:
97  for imu_name in self.imu_names:
98  norm = np.linalg.norm(self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][:, :3], axis=1)
99  norm, in_std = utils.reject_outliers(norm)
100  data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name] = self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][in_std, :]
101 
102  return data

104  def save(self, data, filter=False):
105  """
106  Saves the data to a pickle file.
107 
108  Arguments
109  ----------
110  `data`: `OrderedDict`
111  The data to be saved
112 
113  `filter`: `bool`
114  Whether the data is filtered of values
115  that are not near the constant velocity defined in this file.
116  """
117  ros_robotic_skin_path = rospkg.RosPack().get_path('ros_robotic_skin')
118  filepath = os.path.join(ros_robotic_skin_path, self.filepath+'.pickle')
119  if filter:
120  # filters the data and gets the constant angular velocity values
121  data = self.filter_data(data)
122  with open(filepath, 'wb') as f:
123  pickle.dump(data, f)

125  def filter_data(self, data):
126  """
127  Filters the data along values near `CONSTANT_VELOCITY`
128 
129  Arguments
130  ----------
131  `data`: `OrderedDict`
132  The data from the data collection.
133  """
134  for pose in data.keys():
135  poses_dict = data[pose]
136  for joint in poses_dict.keys():
137  all_joints = poses_dict[joint]
138  for imu in all_joints.keys():
139  imu_points = all_joints[imu][0]
140  delete_idxs = []
141  for ind, val in enumerate(imu_points):
142  joint_vel = val[-1]
143  if abs(joint_vel - CONSTANT_VELOCITY) >= 0.2:
144  delete_idxs.append(ind)
145  res = np.delete(imu_points, delete_idxs, 0)
146  y = np.expand_dims(res, axis=0)
147  all_joints[imu] = y
148  return data

151 class ConstantRotationDataSaver():
152  """
153  Class for collecting dynamic pose data nd save them as a pickle file
154  """
155  def __init__(self, controller, poses_list, filepath='data/constant_data'):
156  """
157  Initializes DynamicPoseDataSaver class.
158 
159  Arguments
160  -----------
161  controller:
162  Wrapped controller to control either Panda or Sawyer robot.
163  poses_list: list
164  A list of poses. Each pose is a list.
165  It includes 7 joint positiosn, 7 joint velociites, and Pose name
166  filepath: str
167  File path to save the collected data
168  """
169  self.controller = controller
170  self.poses_list = poses_list
171 
172  # constant
173  self.pose_names = [pose[2] for pose in poses_list]
174  self.joint_names = map(str, self.controller.joint_names)
175  self.imu_names, self.imu_topics = utils.get_imu_names_and_topics()
176  """
177  to-do get the joints the imus are connected to.
178  """
179  self.collecting_data = False
180  self.curr_pose_name = self.pose_names[0]
181  self.curr_joint_name = self.joint_names[0]
182 
183  self.watch_motion = StopWatch()
184 
185  # data storage
186  self.data_storage = ConstantRotationData(self.pose_names, self.joint_names, self.imu_names, filepath)
187  # Subscribe to IMUs
188  for imu_topic in self.imu_topics:
189  rospy.Subscriber(imu_topic, Imu, self.callback)
190 
191  self.tf_listener = tf.TransformListener()
192  self.Q = {imu_name: Quaternion() for imu_name in self.imu_names}
193 
194  def callback(self, data):
195  """
196  A callback function for IMU topics
197 
198  Arguments
199  ----------
200  data: sensor_msgs.msg.Imu
201  IMU data. Please refer to the official documentation.
202  http://docs.ros.org/melodic/api/sensor_msgs/html/msg/Imu.html
203  """
204  if self.watch_motion.is_started():
205  # acceleration of skin unit, followed by its acceleration
206  acceleration = utils.Vector3_to_np(data.linear_acceleration)
207  quaternion = utils.Quaternion_to_np(self.Q[data.header.frame_id])
208 
209  # get the orientation of the imu
210  joint_angles = self.controller.joint_angles
211  joint_velocity = self.controller.joint_velocity(self.curr_joint_name)
212 
213  self.data_storage.append(
214  pose_name=self.curr_pose_name, # for each defined initial pose
215  joint_name=self.curr_joint_name, # for each excited joint
216  imu_name=data.header.frame_id, # for each imu
217  data=np.r_[
218  quaternion,
219  acceleration,
220  joint_angles,
221  joint_velocity
222  ]
223  )

225  def goto_current_pose(self, pose):
226  positions, _, pose_name = pose[0], pose[1], pose[2] # noqa: F841
227  self.curr_pose_name = pose_name
228  # first, move to the position from <robot>_positions.txt
229  self.controller.publish_positions(positions, sleep=2)
230  print('At Position: ' + pose_name,
231  map(int, utils.RAD2DEG * np.array(positions)))

233  def rotate_at_constant_vel(self):
234  """
235  This will move the joint of the robot arm like a sine wave
236  for all joints for all defined poses.
237  """
238  for pose in self.poses_list:
239  # Go to current setting position
240  self.goto_current_pose(pose)
241 
242  for i, joint_name in enumerate(self.joint_names):
243  self.curr_joint_name = joint_name
244  print(joint_name)
245 
246  # Prepare for publishing velocities
247  velocities = np.zeros(len(self.joint_names))
248  # only one joint - at a time - should move with constant velocity.
249  velocities[i] = CONSTANT_VELOCITY
250 
251  # Start motion and recording
252  self.watch_motion.start()
253  while True:
254  # time within motion
255  t = self.watch_motion.get_elapsed_time()
256 
257  # Rotate a single joint
258  self.controller.publish_velocities(velocities, JOINT_ROT_TIME)
259 
260  if t > DATA_COLLECTION_TIME:
261  break
262 
263  for imu_name in self.imu_names:
264  try:
265  # get pose of imu
266  (_, rot) = self.tf_listener.lookupTransform('/world', imu_name, rospy.Time(0))
267  self.Q[imu_name].x = rot[0]
268  self.Q[imu_name].y = rot[1]
269  self.Q[imu_name].z = rot[2]
270  self.Q[imu_name].w = rot[3]
271  except (tf.LookupException,
272  tf.ConnectivityException,
273  tf.ExtrapolationException):
274  continue
275 
276  self.watch_motion.stop()
277  rospy.sleep(1)

280  """
281  Save data to a pickle file.
282  """
283  data = self.data_storage.clean_data(verbose)
284 
285  self.data_storage.save(data, filter=filter)
